10#ifndef MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_PACKET_RECEIVED_H_
11#define MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_PACKET_RECEIVED_H_
12
13#include <stdint.h>
14
15#include <utility>
16
17#include "absl/base/attributes.h"
18#include "api/array_view.h"
19#include "api/ref_counted_base.h"
20#include "api/rtp_headers.h"
21#include "api/scoped_refptr.h"
22#include "api/units/timestamp.h"
23#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/rtp_packet.h"
24
25namespace webrtc {
26// Class to hold rtp packet with metadata for receiver side.
27// The metadata is not parsed from the rtp packet, but may be derived from the
28// data that is parsed from the rtp packet.
29class RtpPacketReceived : public RtpPacket {
30 public:
31 RtpPacketReceived();
32 explicit RtpPacketReceived(
33 const ExtensionManager* extensions,
34 webrtc::Timestamp arrival_time = webrtc::Timestamp::MinusInfinity());
35 RtpPacketReceived(const RtpPacketReceived& packet);
36 RtpPacketReceived(RtpPacketReceived&& packet);
37
38 RtpPacketReceived& operator=(const RtpPacketReceived& packet);
39 RtpPacketReceived& operator=(RtpPacketReceived&& packet);
40
41 ~RtpPacketReceived();
42
43 // TODO(danilchap): Remove this function when all code update to use RtpPacket
44 // directly. Function is there just for easier backward compatibilty.
45 void GetHeader(RTPHeader* header) const;
46
47 // Time in local time base as close as it can to packet arrived on the
48 // network.
49 webrtc::Timestamp arrival_time() const { return arrival_time_; }
50 void set_arrival_time(webrtc::Timestamp time) { arrival_time_ = time; }
51
52 ABSL_DEPRECATED("Use arrival_time() instead")
53 int64_t arrival_time_ms() const {
54 return arrival_time_.IsMinusInfinity() ? -1 : arrival_time_.ms();
55 }
56 ABSL_DEPRECATED("Use set_arrival_time() instead")
57 void set_arrival_time_ms(int64_t time) {
58 arrival_time_ = webrtc::Timestamp::Millis(time);
59 }
60
61 // Flag if packet was recovered via RTX or FEC.
62 bool recovered() const { return recovered_; }
63 void set_recovered(bool value) { recovered_ = value; }
64
65 int payload_type_frequency() const { return payload_type_frequency_; }
66 void set_payload_type_frequency(int value) {
67 payload_type_frequency_ = value;
68 }
69
70 // An application can attach arbitrary data to an RTP packet using
71 // `additional_data`. The additional data does not affect WebRTC processing.
72 rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RefCountedBase> additional_data() const {
73 return additional_data_;
74 }
75 void set_additional_data(rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RefCountedBase> data) {
76 additional_data_ = std::move(data);
77 }
78
79 private:
80 webrtc::Timestamp arrival_time_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
81 int payload_type_frequency_ = 0;
82 bool recovered_ = false;
83 rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RefCountedBase> additional_data_;
84};
85
86} // namespace webrtc
87#endif // MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_PACKET_RECEIVED_H_
